TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Production Scheduling Model by Bivalent Linear Programming
AU  - Haehling von Lanzenauer, Christoph
Y1  - 1970/09/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.17.1.105
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.17.1.105
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 105
EP  - 111
VL  - 17
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The paper focuses on multi-stage production systems. If such a system is of the more general type than a production line and many products have to be manufactured according to different technological sequence restrictions then two problems arise: (1) scheduling and (2) sequencing. The formulation of that problem requires the simultaneous consideration of the scheduling and sequencing aspect. The paper integrates these two functions into one single model using zero-one programming.
AB  - The paper focuses on multi-stage production systems. If such a system is of the more general type than a production line and many products have to be manufactured according to different technological sequence restrictions then two problems arise: (1) scheduling and (2) sequencing. The formulation of that problem requires the simultaneous consideration of the scheduling and sequencing aspect. The paper integrates these two functions into one single model using zero-one programming.
